      <title>Re: Can you run two instances of EverQuest on one PC?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=tech&amp;message.id=86165#M86165</link>
      <description>As of Windows XP Service Pack 2, you no longer need to disable the alt-tab entry with the Windows Application Compatibility Toolkit.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Also, you do not need to use any 3rd party applications, such as EQ Windows, which hasn't been updated in 8 months, or WinEQ, for which I find the licensing requirements unacceptable. Some time ago, SOE chose to allow backgrounding the game with the alt keystrokes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I've found that it works alot better if you keep both instances windowed. If you try to do it full screen, switching between the two, it will probably crash. It usually does for me (Nvidia hardware) It used to work well full-screen or windowed, but about 8 months ago, they screwed that up with a patch, and it hasn't been totally fixed yet.&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by -Evil_Wizard- on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;02-17-2005&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;07:14 AM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
